{{SelfDistinguish|指中華民國38年（1949年）4月6日總統令[[褒揚令列表|褒揚]]的陸軍第八十二軍第二百四十八師少將師長馬得勝，刊4月11日《總統府公報》第219號第1版}}

[[File:GeorgeMatheson.jpg|thumb]]
'''马得胜'''（{{lang-en|'''George Matheson'''}}，{{bd|1842年|3月27日|1906年|8月28日|catIdx=Matheson}}）是一位[[苏格兰|苏格兰]][[神学|神学家]]和传教士。

==生平==
马得胜出生在[[格拉斯哥|格拉斯哥]]，是一个商人和 Jane Matheson （第二代表兄妹）的儿子，是8个孩子中最年长的一个。他就读于[[格拉斯哥大学|格拉斯哥大学]]<!-- , he graduated first in classics, [[逻辑学|逻辑学]]和[[哲学|哲学]] -->。他在20岁时完全失明，但仍坚持完成学业，研读神学和历史。1879年，[[爱丁堡大学|爱丁堡大学]]授予他[[神学博士|神学博士]]荣誉学位。1890年，他当选成为皇家爱丁堡学会会员。1906年8月28日，他在爱丁堡突然中风去世，埋葬在格拉斯哥的公墓。他终生未婚。  

==事奉==
1866年，马得胜成为一名助理牧师。<!-- 他最初ministry began in 1868 at [[Innellan|Innellan]], on [[阿盖尔郡|阿盖尔郡]]（Argyllshire） coast between [[Dunoon|Dunoon]] and [[Toward|Toward]]. He stayed 18 years.  His books on ''Aids to the Study of German Theology, Can the Old Faith live with the New?, The Growth of the Spirit of Christianity from the First Century to the Dawn of the Lutheran Era'', established his reputation as a liberal and spiritually minded theologian; and [[维多利亚女王|维多利亚女王]] invited him to preach at [[Balmoral|Balmoral]].  She had his sermon on Job published. -->

1886年，他移居到[[爱丁堡|爱丁堡]]，担任圣伯纳德教区教堂<!-- [[St._Bernard's_Parish_Church|St. Bernard's Parish Church]] -->牧师达13年之久。 

1879年，他拒绝接替Dr. John Gumming (1807-1881)担任[[伦敦|伦敦]]英国巡回刑事法庭的牧师。<!-- 1881 he was chosen as Baird lecturer, and took for his subject ''Natural Elements of Revealed Theology'', and in 1882 he was the St Giles lecturer, his subject being ''[[儒教|儒教]]''。1890年，他当选为 a fellow of [[Royal_Society_of_Edinburgh|Royal Society of Edinburgh]],[[阿伯丁大学|阿伯丁大学]]授予他荣誉[[法学博士|法学博士]],1899 he was appointed Gifford lecturer by that 大学, but declined on grounds of health.同年r he severed his active connection with St. Bernard's. --> 

==著作==
他最著名的一首圣诗《哦那不肯放我之爱》（''O love that will not let me go''），已被列为基督教会中最受欢迎的圣诗之一，这首诗是他在一个妹妹结婚的那天创作的。他只出版过一本诗集, ''Sacred Songs''。<!--  His exegesis owes its interest to his subjective resources rather than to breadth of learning; his power lay in spiritual vision rather than balanced judgment, and in the vivid apprehension of the factors which make the Christian personality, rather than in constructive doctrinal statement. -->

